  <brief_title>Stylet Angle for McGrath Videolaryngoscopy</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Ajou University School of Medicine</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Ajou University School of Medicine</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The McGrath videolaryngoscope (VL) provides excellent laryngoscopic views, but directing an
      endotracheal tube is not easy, so routine using of stylet is recommended. The goal of this
      study is to determine the appropriate angle of stylet by comparing time to intubation (TTI).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
